</h3></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-23_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fsvrPk ezIRGP pf-24_"><p class="sc-dQEsWe kFLVLU pf-25_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fFlofg cnCjdX pf-27_">Image by&nbsp;khwanchai14 via Envato Elements</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-5b91" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-fbKhWw dHaUDq pf-28_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-dhFVuh jkEGqE"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-29_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:8px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fsvrPk ezIRGP pf-30_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-ePDMnc jGJiiy pf-31_">Revolutionising health and safety: The role of AI and digitalisation at work</h3><p class="sc-dPZUdm eeluBw pf-33_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-91229529-6f14-4eee-afa4-c9e1eddb9fbd"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Every year on 28 April, organisations and individuals around the world come together to recognise World Day for Safety and Health at Work. Established by the International Labour Organisation (ILO) in 2003, this global awareness day highlights the critical importance of preventing accidents and diseases in the workplace. For 2025, the theme is "Revolutionising Health and Safety: The Role of AI and Digitalisation at Work", a timely focus on how emerging technologies are transforming Occupational Safety and Health (OSH) practices across industries.
<br><br>At The Mandatory Training Group, we support this initiative wholeheartedly, helping organisations adapt to the future of work with comprehensive training solutions and digital compliance tools, such as ComplyPlusâ„¢.
</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-36_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fsvrPk ezIRGP pf-37_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-ePDMnc jGJiiy pf-38_">What is World Day for Safety and Health at Work?</h3><p class="sc-dPZUdm eeluBw pf-40_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-ee6fa4c9-e1ed-4b9f-bd50-9ed58b2e5fff"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">World Day for Safety and Health at Work is an international awareness-raising campaign promoting the prevention of occupational accidents and diseases. It emphasises creating a culture of safety, resilience, and continuous improvement in workplaces worldwide. It also encourages stakeholders to prioritise workers' well-being by investing in proactive safety measures and compliance practices.</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-43_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fsvrPk ezIRGP pf-44_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-ePDMnc jGJiiy pf-45_">Theme for 2025 - Revolutionising health and safety</h3><p class="sc-dPZUdm eeluBw pf-47_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-2556c7b1-6cce-4eaf-90fb-ef395bf9af45"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">This year's theme, "Revolutionising Health and Safety: The Role of AI and Digitalisation at Work", underscores the enormous potential of technology to reshape workplace safety standards. Artificial intelligence (AI), machine learning, predictive analytics, and digital monitoring systems are no longer futuristic concepts; they are vital tools in safeguarding employees, identifying hazards, and streamlining compliance efforts.
</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-50_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fsvrPk ezIRGP pf-51_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-ePDMnc jGJiiy pf-52_">Key ways AI and digitalisation are impacting health and safety include:</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-fAGzVM iDZITE pf-54_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bkSTSn iEaWBl pf-55_">Predictive risk assessments based on real-time data analysis.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bkSTSn iEaWBl pf-57_">Wearable safety devices monitor vital signs and environmental hazards.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bkSTSn iEaWBl pf-59_">Automated compliance tracking reduces human error.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bkSTSn iEaWBl pf-61_">Virtual training simulations enhance employee preparedness.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bkSTSn iEaWBl pf-63_">Innovative reporting tools enable faster incident management and learning.
</li></ul><p class="sc-dPZUdm eeluBw pf-65_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-902a3e7f-b7a9-4278-a834-d95ea5a996a3"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">At The Mandatory Training Group, we integrate these innovations into our training and compliance services, ensuring our clients remain ahead of regulatory changes and best practices.
</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-68_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fsvrPk ezIRGP pf-69_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-ePDMnc jGJiiy pf-70_">Key facts and statistics</h3><p class="sc-dPZUdm eeluBw pf-72_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-7983ffd8-21e1-4b18-8c43-0089fdc313de"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">To better understand the urgency of improving workplace safety and embracing technological advancements, it is important to consider the following key facts and statistics:</span></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-fAGzVM iDZITE pf-75_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bkSTSn iEaWBl pf-76_">According to the International Labour Organisation (ILO), around 2.9 million workers die annually from occupational accidents and work-related diseases (<a href="https://www.ilo.org/" target="_blank"><em><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);">ILO, 2024</span></em></a>).
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bkSTSn iEaWBl pf-78_">4% of global GDP is lost annually due to work-related accidents and diseases (<a href="https://www.ilo.org/" target="_blank"><em><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);">ILO, 2024</span></em></a>).
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bkSTSn iEaWBl pf-80_"><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);"></span><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);"></span>AI-based predictive analytics can reduce workplace accidents by up to 20%, according to a 2024 industry analysis (<a href="https://www.weforum.org/" target="_blank"><em><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);">World Economic Forum, 2024</span></em></a>).
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bkSTSn iEaWBl pf-82_">Wearable tech adoption for workplace safety is expected to grow by over 15% by 2026 (<a href="https://www.gartner.com/" target="_blank"><em><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);">Gartner Research, 2024</span></em></a>).
</li></ul><p class="sc-dPZUdm eeluBw pf-84_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-4c7b9ac3-1af8-4c99-928f-000d53c7c0cd"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">These figures demonstrate the urgent need for embracing digital transformation to protect employees and optimise safety management.
</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-87_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fsvrPk ezIRGP pf-88_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-ePDMnc jGJiiy pf-89_">Best practices for organisations in 2025</h3><p class="sc-dPZUdm eeluBw pf-91_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-5294e126-fb36-4813-ae9b-2994af7dbb54"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">To align with the 2025 theme, organisations should:</span></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-fAGzVM iDZITE pf-94_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bkSTSn iEaWBl pf-95_">Invest in smart technologies such as AI-driven risk assessment tools and wearable safety devices.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bkSTSn iEaWBl pf-97_">Implement continuous digital training to upskill employees on new health and safety protocols.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bkSTSn iEaWBl pf-99_">Utilise automated compliance platforms, such as ComplyPlusTM, to maintain up-to-date records and minimise administrative burdens.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bkSTSn iEaWBl pf-101_">Promote a safety-first culture by encouraging proactive reporting and open communication.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bkSTSn iEaWBl pf-103_">Regularly review and update policies to reflect technological advancements and emerging risks, ensuring they remain current and effective.</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-105_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fsvrPk ezIRGP pf-106_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-ePDMnc jGJiiy pf-107_">Conclusion</h3><p class="sc-dPZUdm eeluBw pf-109_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-786834d9-5ea5-4996-a3ef-60e0878931de"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">World Day for Safety and Health at Work 2025 is a pivotal opportunity for organisations to reimagine and revolutionise their approach to occupational safety. As AI and digitalisation reshape the landscape, businesses must be proactive in adopting new technologies and strategies to protect their workforce.
<br><br>At <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/" target="_blank"><em><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);">The Mandatory Training Group</span></em></a>, we offer CPD-accredited health and safety courses and training programmes to empower organisations to prevent and identify avoidable harm and diseases in the workplace, provide a safe work environment, and improve efficiency and team productivity.
